Apple today released visionOS 2.6, the sixth update to the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/visionos-2/">visionOS 2</a> operating system that came out in September. visionOS 2.6 comes two months after the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/05/12/apple-releases-visionos-2-5/">launch of visionOS 2.5</a>.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2024/06/visionOS-2-on-Apple-Vision-Pro-Feature.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-955609" /><br/>
visionOS 2.6 can be downloaded on all Vision Pro headsets by navigating to the Settings app, selecting the General section, and choosing the Software Update option.<br/>
<br/>
According to Apple's release notes, visionOS 2.6 focuses on bug fixes and under-the-hood improvements. There are no new features in the update. <br/>
<br/>
